[Tool]
Name: picrust
Repository: https://github.com/picrust/picrust
Version(Tag): 1.0.0
Email: picrust-users@googlegroups.com
Webpage: http://picrust.github.io/picrust/index.html
Copyright: Langille, M. G.I., Zaneveld, J., Caporaso, J. G., McDonald, D., Knights, D., a Reyes, J.,Clemente, J. C., Burkepile, D. E., Vega Thurber, R. L., Knight, R., Beiko, R. G.,  Huttenhower, C
CopyrightYear: 2013
Dependencies: python (>= 2.7), python-cogent, python-numpy, python-setuptools 
R-Libs: ape
Description(<60char): Investestigation of  Communities by Reconstruction of Unobserved States
Description(Longer):   The PICRUSt project aims to support prediction of the unobserved character states in a community of organisms from phylogenetic information about the organisms in that community. The primary application is to predict gene family abundance (e.g. the metagenome) in environmental DNA samples for which only marker gene (e.g. 16S rRNA gene) data are available.
CommandlineScripts: picrust/scripts/normalize_by_copy_number.py
PostInst: git clone https://github.com/bipy/pyqi ~/pyqi
  cd ~/pyqi
  python setup.py install
  cd ~
  git clone git://github.com/biom-format/biom-format.git 
  cd ~/biom-format
  python setup.py install
  dirpart1="//usr/share/biobakery/picrust-"
  dirpart2=`date +'%d%m%y'`
  dirpart3="/picrust"
  dirpart4="/data"
  picrustdir=$dirpart1$dirpart2$dirpart3$dirpart3
  cd $picrustdir
  mkdir data
  picrustdir1=$picrustdir$dirpart4
  cd $picrustdir1
  wget ftp://thebeast.colorado.edu/pub/picrust-references/picrust-1.0.0/16S_13_5_precalculated.tab.gz 
  wget ftp://thebeast.colorado.edu/pub/picrust-references/picrust-1.0.0/ko_13_5_precalculated.tab.gz 
  wget https://github.com/picrust/picrust/releases/download/0.9.2/16S_18may2012_precalculated.tab.gz
  wget https://github.com/picrust/picrust/releases/download/0.9.2/ko_18may2012_precalculated.tab.gz
  wget https://github.com/picrust/picrust/releases/download/0.9.2/cog_18may2012_precalculated.tab.gz 
  picrustdir2=$dirpart1$dirpart2$dirpart3
  cd $picrustdir2
  python setup.py install
